# SETUP.md — How to Run This Project

## Prerequisites

Install R (≥ 4.3) from: https://cran.r-project.org

Then install required packages by running this in your R console:

```r
install.packages(c(
  "tidyverse",    # data manipulation
  "nlmixr2",      # PopPK modeling (FOCEI)
  "ggplot2",      # visualization
  "patchwork",    # multi-panel plots
  "vpc",          # Visual Predictive Check
  "xpose",        # diagnostic plots
  "MASS",         # correlated random effects
  "knitr",        # report rendering
  "kableExtra",   # table formatting
  "GGally",       # correlation plots
  "ggridges"      # ridge plots
))
```

## Run the full pipeline

Open RStudio, set working directory to this project folder, then run in order:

```r
source("R/01_simulate_data.R")    # ~5 seconds
source("R/02_eda_plots.R")        # ~30 seconds
source("R/03_poppk_model.R")      # ~5-10 minutes (FOCEI estimation)
source("R/04_vpc_simulation.R")   # ~2-5 minutes (500 VPC simulations)
```

## Render the Quarto report

```r
install.packages("quarto")
quarto::quarto_render("report/CNS_PopPK_Report.qmd")
# Opens as HTML in browser — also renders PDF if LaTeX installed
```

## Output files

| Folder | Contents |
|--------|----------|
| `data/` | Simulated PK dataset (CSV, NONMEM-format) |
| `plots/` | All 11 figures (PNG, 200 DPI) |
| `output/` | Model objects (RDS), Word summary (DOCX) |
| `report/` | Quarto source + rendered HTML |

## Notes

- All data are fully **simulated** — this is a portfolio/educational project
- Models take several minutes to run (FOCEI requires iterative estimation)
- If `nlmixr2` installation fails, try: `install.packages("nlmixr2", dependencies = TRUE)`
- Tested on R 4.3.2, Windows 11 and Ubuntu 22.04
